# T-2225 — Expected-transient fleet hosts for check-fleet-doorbell-mail-health.sh.
#
# One profile NAME (the [hubs.NAME] from ~/.termlink/hubs.toml) per line.
# A host listed here that is unreachable / setup-fail is classified
# `transient_skipped` by the fleet doorbell+mail canary and does NOT flip the
# fleet verdict to DRIFT — a laptop being asleep is expected, not a failure
# (G-019 alert-fatigue prevention). A listed host that is REACHABLE still counts
# pass/fail normally: this suppresses down-ness, not brokenness.
#
# Lines starting with # are comments; blank lines ignored. The
# FLEET_DM_CANARY_TRANSIENT env var (comma-separated) is merged on top of this.
#
# laptop-141 — WSL-on-Windows laptop (192.168.10.141), intermittently off the
# network (No route to host when the laptop is asleep/off). Its reachable-but-
# wedged failure mode is separately tracked by T-2017; this entry stops the
# whole-fleet canary DRIFTing every time the laptop is simply powered down.
laptop-141
